   180044f66:	8b da                	mov    ebx,edx
   180044f68:	48 8b f1             	mov    rsi,rcx
   180044f6b:	83 fa 01             	cmp    edx,0x1
   180044f6e:	75 05                	jne    0x180044f75
   180044f70:	e8 5f 05 00 00       	call   0x1800454d4
   180044f75:	4c 8b c7             	mov    r8,rdi
   180044f78:	8b d3                	mov    edx,ebx
   180044f7a:	48 8b ce             	mov    rcx,rsi
   180044f7d:	48 8b 5c 24 30       	mov    rbx,QWORD PTR [rsp+0x30]
   180044f82:	48 8b 74 24 38       	mov    rsi,QWORD PTR [rsp+0x38]
   180044f87:	48 83 c4 20          	add    rsp,0x20
   180044f8b:	5f                   	pop    rdi
   180044f8c:	e9 9b fe ff ff       	jmp    0x180044e2c
```

**Note on this snippet:** this is the compiler-generated `DllMain`/CRT startup thunk (register
save, `reason == DLL_PROCESS_ATTACH` check via `cmp edx,0x1`, tail-jump into the real init routine
at `0x180044e2c`). It is not itself the `ProcessEvent` hook — it's included here only as a verified,
attributable disassembly sample. Locating and disassembling the actual hook-installation routine
would require deeper analysis than string matching (which is what identified the
`"[+] ProcessEvent hook initialized."` string in section 4).

